The Comoros group islands the Indian Ocean mostly independent nation but also including the French territory Mayotte historically linked both East Africa and France and now has strong Malagasy influence Zanzibars taarab music however remains the most influential genre the islands and Comorian version called twarab popular Leading twarab bands include Sambeco and Belle Lumire well singers including Chamsia Sagaf and Mohammed Hassan Comorian instruments include the oud and violin the most frequent accompaniment for twarab well gabusi type lute and ndzendze box zither and the msondo drum Sega music from nearby Mauritius and Runion also popular The primitive oboe the ndzumara now nearly extinct Modern musicians include Abou Chihabi who composed the Comorian national anthem and who known for his reggaetinged panAfrican variet music reggaezouksoukous fusionists like Maalesh and Salim Ali Amir Nawal Ali Sad Achimo who resides Paris Diho singersongwriters and instrumentalists 